Koleka Mlisana from the Ministerial Advisory Committee on COVID-19 spoke with eTV's Annika Larsen. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - We are in a mess, according to a warning from Professor Koleka Mlisana, co-chair of the Ministerial Advisory Committee on COVID-19. READ: COVID-19: SA records 12537 new cases She says the mass looting and destruction are posing a threat to the healthcare system. READ: COVID-19 vaccinations face delay after pharmacy lootings "The concern is that they are not using any non-pharmaceutical interventions and now, everybody who is found looting is carried in police vans to prisons and the question is going to be where then is social distancing, use of masks, in prisons?" Professor Mlisana said. At least 72 people have died in the unrest and over 1,200 have been arrested. Watch the video above for more details on this story.